properties.Name: AssetAccountingCategory
properties.Description:
A categorization of assets as to whether they will be used, sold or reassigned within one year, beyond one year or are a deferred charge.

NONCURRENT ASSET
Assets meant to be used up or consumed beyond one operating cycle or one year.

DEFERRED CHARGE
A charge that is deferred to another operating cycle or period.

CURRENT ASSET
Assets meant to be used up or consumed within one operating cycle or one year.
